From 9e45bf97135b8fa602fb976f6bb95fc3e06ab4de Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: janet-darwin8-ppc <janet-darwin8-ppc@local>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 02:27:33 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] test/suite-os: add tests for os/execute :cd argument

The test suite previously had no coverage for the :cd argument to
os/execute / os/spawn, even though it is gated by a JANET_SPAWN_CHDIR
feature macro covering three distinct backends:

  - posix_spawn_file_actions_addchdir on glibc Linux and FreeBSD;
  - posix_spawn_file_actions_addchdir_np on macOS 10.15+;
  - chdir() inside the forked child for non-posix_spawn fallbacks
    (e.g. macOS 10.4 Tiger, where posix_spawn{,p} is unavailable
    and Janet must fall back to fork+execve).

Two cases added:

  - :cd to an existing directory --- exercises the chdir success
    path through to a successful exec.
  - :cd to a nonexistent directory --- exercises the chdir failure
    path.  For posix_spawn backends the error surfaces via the
    spawn-call status; for the fork+execve fallback it surfaces via
    a CLOEXEC errpipe carrying the chdir errno back from the child
    to the parent, which then reaps the zombie before panicking.

Platforms lacking :cd support (Windows, mingw, macOS 10.5-10.14
without the fork+execve fallback, non-glibc Linux) panic at
arg-parse time with ":cd argument not supported on this system".
A runtime probe detects this and uses skip-asserts to gate the
two new tests, so the suite stays green on those platforms.
---
 test/suite-os.janet | 21 +++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+)

diff --git a/test/suite-os.janet b/test/suite-os.janet
index 965dff1a..606df059 100644
--- a/test/suite-os.janet
+++ b/test/suite-os.janet
@@ -191,6 +191,27 @@
                                :px
                                {:out dn :err dn})))
 
+# os/execute with :cd
+# Skip on platforms without :cd support.  Janet's :cd argument
+# requires JANET_SPAWN_CHDIR, defined on Linux (glibc), macOS 10.15+,
+# FreeBSD, and the fork+execve fallback path.  Other platforms panic
+# with ":cd argument not supported on this system" at arg-parse time.
+(when (try
+        (do (os/execute [;run janet "-e" "(os/exit 0)"] :p
+                        {:cd (os/cwd)})
+            false)
+        ([err]
+          (if (string/has-prefix? ":cd argument not supported" err)
+            true
+            (error err))))
+  (skip-asserts 2))
+(assert-no-error "os/execute with :cd to existing dir"
+                 (os/execute [;run janet "-e" "(os/exit 0)"] :p
+                             {:cd (os/cwd)}))
+(assert-error "os/execute with :cd to nonexistent dir"
+              (os/execute [;run janet "-e" "(+ 1 1)"] :p
+                          {:cd "/nonexistent-abc123def456"}))
+
 # Issue 16922
 (assert-error "os/realpath errors when path does not exist"
               (os/realpath "abc123def456"))
